      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The modeled QoI (normalized index of hemolysis, NIH) is directly traceable to the clinical hemolysis acceptance criterion specified in the device submission.",
      "rationale": "NIH is the primary regulatory QoI and is directly modeled. Mapping from CFD stress-based hemolysis model to NIH is documented but relies on a single published power-law correlation without sensitivity analysis."
